item.description:
Amazing free-kick Cristiano Ronaldo © 105 Km/hr Tomahawk vs Zaragoza 12/12/10
Cristiano Ronaldo scored his 17th goal of the season with a typically beautiful free kick just before halftime to put Real Madrid up 2-0 over Real Zaragoza (they eventually won 3-1). The curving shot into the top corner left Zaragoza keeper Leo Franco fuming with his feet planted in the pitch. Ronaldo then celebrated in true Cristiano Ronaldo fashion with a smug facial expression and head-bob reminiscent of a bad Robert De Niro impression, followed by a sparkling smile and thumbs-up combo, then some kind of monster hands thing. And that's how you celebrate a goal. If you're Cristiano Ronaldo.
